# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Successfully configured Vercel Web Analytics for this HTML5/Express.js project according to the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### Updated Files

**frontend/public/index.html** - Updated analytics script path
- Changed script source from `/_vercel/insights/script.js` to `https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js`
- Maintained existing `window.va` initialization function
- Analytics code placed before closing `</body>` tag as recommended

**frontend/public/builder.html** - Updated analytics script path  
- Changed script source from `/_vercel/insights/script.js` to `https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js`
- Maintained existing `window.va` initialization function
- Analytics code placed before closing `</body>` tag as recommended

### Package Dependencies

**@vercel/analytics@2.0.1** - Already listed in package.json
- Verified installation by running `npm install`
- Package properly installed and available in node_modules
- No package.json changes needed (dependency was already declared)

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
This is an **HTML5/Express.js** project with:
- Backend: Node.js/Express serving static HTML files
- Frontend: Vanilla JavaScript (no framework like React, Next.js, Vue, etc.)
- Static files served from `frontend/public/` directory

### Analytics Implementation (HTML5 Method)
According to the latest Vercel documentation, for HTML5 projects we use:

1. **Initialize the global analytics function** before loading the script:
   ```html
   <script>
     window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
   </script>
   ```

2. **Load the analytics script** from the CDN:
   ```html
   <script defer src="https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js"></script>
   ```

This implementation:
- Uses the official CDN-hosted script for HTML5 projects
- Loads asynchronously with `defer` attribute for optimal performance
- Initializes the queue system to capture analytics events
- Works automatically once deployed to Vercel

## Testing Performed

✅ Verified @vercel/analytics package installation  
✅ Confirmed server starts successfully  
✅ Tested HTTP requests to both HTML pages  
✅ Validated analytics script tags are correctly rendered  
✅ Verified no build errors or conflicts

## Next Steps

To see analytics data:

1. **Deploy to Vercel**: Run `vercel deploy` or push to connected Git repository
2. **Enable Analytics**: Visit project dashboard → Analytics → Enable Web Analytics
3. **Verify**: Check browser Network tab for requests to `cdn.vercel-insights.com`
4. **View Data**: After deployment and traffic, view analytics in Vercel dashboard

## Notes

- The previous script path `/_vercel/insights/script.js` was intended for Speed Insights (performance monitoring)
- Updated to the correct CDN path for Web Analytics (visitor tracking)
- Both HTML pages (landing and builder) now have consistent analytics implementation
- No additional configuration needed - analytics will start collecting data automatically upon deployment
